  description: "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor class identity checks in cfasc132 namespace — wave 258 theme: ProcessPoolExecutor identity; ProcessPoolExecutor is defined in Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py; ProcessPoolExecutor.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__('ProcessPoolExecutor.__init__')==True (len=28: 'ProcessPoolExecutor'=19+'.'=1+'__init__'=8); ProcessPoolExecutor.__module__.__eq__('concurrent.futures.process')==True (len=26: 'concurrent'=10+'.'=1+'futures'=7+'.'=1+'process'=7, one char longer than ThreadPoolExecutor's module len=25); ProcessPoolExecutor.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('Executor')==True (same as ThreadPoolExecutor, both inherit from Executor); ProcessPoolExecutor.__mro__.__len__()==3 ([ProcessPoolExecutor, Executor, object]); ProcessPoolExecutor.__qualname__.__len__()==19 ('ProcessPoolExecutor'=19); verified with Python 3.14.3"
